Kenya is a strange place, at least in its political sphere. The latest twist is about Nasa operative Miguna Miguna, who was last night put on a flight headed for Amsterdam then Canada. Mr Miguna, the government says, is now on his way 'home'. According to Amsterdam Airport Schiphol's website, a KLM flight that departed from Nairobi on Tuesday night is scheduled to arrive at 06:30 (8.30am Kenyan time). More follows.